# Ecommerce Platform — Cursor Project Rules

<!--
  This file is the Cursor equivalent of the workspace-root CLAUDE.md.
  Keep the two in sync: when you change an inter-service rule in CLAUDE.md,
  mirror it here so Cursor users get the same guardrails.
-->

## Workspace model
- This is a PARENT workspace repo. Real service code lives in git submodules under `services/`.
- Always open the workspace ROOT in Cursor — never a single service folder — so the AI sees every service at once.
- Never commit service implementation code into this parent repo. It only holds:
  CLAUDE.md, .cursor/rules/, shared-contracts/, and submodule pointers (services + aidlc-workflows).

## Cross-service rules
- Services talk to each other ONLY over HTTP. Never import another service's source.
- No database foreign keys across service boundaries.
- If a dependency service is down, degrade gracefully (timeout + fallback), don't crash.

## Shared-contract rules
- `shared-contracts/` is the source of truth for every API shape and event schema.
- Update the spec in `shared-contracts/` BEFORE changing any response field or adding an event.

## Submodule rules
- Push the service repo first, THEN bump its pointer in the workspace. Never the reverse.
- After pulling, run `git submodule update --init --recursive` if `services/` looks empty.
